## One of the most exciting areas in all of data science right now is wearable computing.
## The raw data was collected from the accelerometers from the Samsung Galaxy S smartphone.
## https://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/getdata%2Fprojectfiles%2FUCI%20HAR%20Dataset.zip 

A script, run_analysis.R, was used to tidy up the raw data and created a tidy dataset called 
"tidy.csv". This tidy dataset contains 180 observations in 81 columns.

1. id: Each unique id maps to a subject(an user) participating in the program.
    id = 1 - 30
    
2. activity_id: Each unique id indicates an activity that the participant was asked to perform.
      1 = WALKING
      2 = WALKING_UPSTAIRS
      3 = WALKING_DOWNSTAIRS
      4 = SITTING
      5 = STANDING
      6 = LAYING
      
The following 79 columns are the result of average or standard variation based on the measurement 
retrieved from the partipants' phone. They are numrical values. The column names are:

3. tBodyAcc.mean...X              
4. tBodyAcc.mean...Y              
5. tBodyAcc.mean...Z              
